 plan of the city of New York.--Plan of Amboy, with its environs, from an actual survey. Scale ca. 1:650,000. LC Maps of North America, 1750-1789, 1045 Available also through the Library of Congress Web site as a raster image. Vault AACR2: 100; 651/1; 651/2; 651/3; 651/4; 651/5; 651/6; 651/7; 651/8; 700/1; 710/2"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-04-29T15:40:09.708Z", "group": ["gmd.mar", "catalog-split-12", "catalog", "general-maps", "main-catalog-split-12"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/74692880/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd380/g3800/g3800/ct000082.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd380/g3800/g3800/ct000082.gif#h=381&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd380:g3800:g3800:ct000082/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=2017&w=794", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd380:g3800:g3800:ct000082/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=4035&w=1589"], "index": 4, "language": ["english"], "location": ["new york city", "qu\u00e9bec", "qu\u00e9bec (province)", "new york (state)", "canada", "perth amboy", "united states", "northeastern states", "new jersey", "new york"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/tiff", "image/jpeg", "image/jp2"], "number": ["2005-01-04t16:52:50", "2025-06-07t18:30:16.200000", "74692880"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["map"], "partof": ["military battles and campaigns", "geography and map division", "catalog", "american revolution and its era: maps and charts of north america and the west indies, 1750-1789"], "score": 34.2189, "shelf_id": "G3800 1776 .P6", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["qu\u00e9bec (province)", "new york (state)", "new york (n.y.)", "canada", "perth amboy", "administrative and political divisions", "new york", "early works to 1800", "united states", "northeastern states", "new jersey", "perth amboy (n.j.)", "maps"], "timestamp": "2026-04-29T16:14:20.380Z", "title": "The provinces of New York and New Jersey; with part of Pensilvania, and the province of Quebec", "type": ["cartographic"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/74692880/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2006625921", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2006625921/", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/13f8e8ec-e3f5-51b7-b1a1-5c0d6c9331e8", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.gmd/g3814p.ct006952", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/g3814p.ct006952/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["brinley, francis w.", "baker (lithographer : new york, n.y.)"], "date": "1836", "dates": ["1836"], "description": ["General street map showing buildings and lot lines. Relief shown by hachures. Depths shown by soundings. Also covers part of Raritan Bay. LC copy imperfect: Upper left corner torn away, laminated, mounted on cloth backing to form single sheet, fold-lined, small sections missing at fold lines, sheet trimmed, annotated in ink to show additional buildings and names. Includes inset \"Map shewing the situation of Perth Amboy with New York, the Atlantic Ocean &c., scale 3 miles to an inch\". Available also through the Library of Congress Web site as a raster image."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-04-29T15:40:12.234Z", "group": ["gmd.mar", "catalog-split-01", "catalog", "general-maps", "main-catalog-split-01"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2006625921/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd381/g3814/g3814p/ct006952.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd381/g3814/g3814p/ct006952.gif#h=150&w=100", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd381:g3814:g3814p:ct006952/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=1337&w=894", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd381:g3814:g3814p:ct006952/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=2675&w=1788"], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "location": ["perth amboy", "united states", "new jersey", "perth amboy region", "new york", "raritan bay"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/tiff", "image/jpeg", "image/jp2"], "number": ["2025-06-07t01:46:57.300000", "sheet", "2006625921", "2016-10-03t09:58:45"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["map"], "partof": ["geography and map division", "cities and towns", "catalog"], "score": 34.2189, "shelf_id": "G3814.P4 1836 .B7", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["raritan bay (n.j. and n.y.)", "perth amboy", "bathymetric maps", "new york", "real property", "united states", "new jersey", "perth amboy region", "perth amboy (n.j.)", "perth amboy region (n.j.)", "maps", "raritan bay"], "timestamp": "2026-04-29T15:51:03.749Z", "title": "Map of the city of Perth Amboy, N.J. : February 1836", "type": ["cartographic"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2006625921/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/gm71000984", "http://www.loc.gov/item/gm71000984/", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/e3e24845-78ac-5814-bd0b-74b6c33051a6", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.gmd/g3814p.ar125000", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/g3814p.ar125000/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1780", "dates": ["1780"], "description": ["\"The map presented here shows the city and harbor of Charleston, South Carolina, at the time of the first British siege of Charleston and attack on Fort Sullivan in June 1776. This was the earliest British attempt to capture Charleston during the Revolutionary War, by which General Henry Clinton and Admiral Sir Peter Parker sought to put down the rebellion in the southern colonies. Above the map of Charleston is a view of Fort Sullivan, where William Moultrie, a colonel in the state militia of South Carolina, repulsed a British attack. The fort was later renamed Fort Moultrie in his honor. After failing to secure Charleston, the British fleet sailed to New York City. British forces would not return to Charleston until 1780. The map also includes an inset view of Amboy (present-day Perth Amboy) on the Raritan River, in New Jersey. It shows a layout of the town with houses, streets, fields, vegetation, connecting roads, nearby parts of Raritan Bay and Staten Island, and the ferry to South Amboy. This map has a watermark. Relief is shown by hachures. The map is from the Rochambeau Collection at the Library of Congress, which consists of 40 manuscript maps, 26 printed maps, and a manuscript atlas that belonged to Jean-Baptiste-Donatien de Vimeur, comte de Rochambeau (1725-1807), commander in chief of the French expeditionary army (1780-82) during the American Revolution. Some of the maps were used by Rochambeau during the war. Dating from 1717 to 1795, the maps cover much of eastern North America, from Newfoundland and Labrador in the north to Haiti in the south. The collection includes maps of cities, maps showing Revolutionary War battles and military campaigns, and early state maps from the 1790s.\" World Digital Library."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-04-29T15:39:45.215Z", "group": ["gmd.mar", "catalog-split-01", "catalog", "general-maps", "main-catalog-split-01"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/gm71000984/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd381/g3814/g3814p/ar125000.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd381/g3814/g3814p/ar125000.gif#h=150&w=220", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd381:g3814:g3814p:ar125000/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=464&w=681", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd381:g3814:g3814p:ar125000/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=929&w=1363"], "index": 6, "language": ["french"], "location": ["fort moultrie", "perth amboy", "charleston harbor", "charleston", "united states", "south carolina", "new jersey"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/tiff", "image/jpeg", "image/jp2"], "number": ["gm71000984", "2025-09-24t13:14:18.100000"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["map"], "partof": ["military battles and campaigns", "american revolution and its era: maps and charts of north america and the west indies, 1750-1789", "world digital library", "catalog", "geography and map division", "rochambeau map collection", "france in america"], "score": 34.2189, "shelf_id": "G3814.P4 1780 .P5", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["aerial views", "fort moultrie", "perth amboy", "fort moultrie (s.c.)", "charleston harbor", "charleston", "charleston harbor (s.c.)", "early works to 1800", "united states", "siege", "charleston (s.c.)", "history", "new jersey", "south carolina", "perth amboy (n.j.)", "early maps", "maps"], "timestamp": "2026-04-29T16:36:27.580Z", "title": "[Plan d'Amboy]. [Vues de la rade de Charles-Town et de Fort Sulivan, mai 1780]", "type": ["cartographic"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/gm71000984/"}], "resource": {"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/njr/batch_njr_basil_ver02/data/sn85035720/00279529935/1908021702/0391.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:njr:batch_njr_basil_ver02:data:sn85035720:00279529935:1908021702:0391/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/njr/batch_njr_basil_ver02/data/sn85035720/00279529935/1908021702/0391.pdf", "segment_count": 8, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85035720/1908-02-17/ed-2/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/njr/batch_njr_basil_ver02/data/sn85035720/00279529935/1908021702/0391.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:njr:batch_njr_basil_ver02:data:sn85035720:00279529935:1908021702:0391/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/njr/batch_njr_basil_ver02/data/sn85035720/00279529935/1908021702/0391.pdf", "segment_count": 8, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85035720/1908-02-17/ed-2/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/njr/batch_njr_basil_ver02/data/sn85035720/00279529935/1908021702/0391.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85035720/1908-02-17/ed-2/?sp=1"], "batch": ["njr_basil_ver02"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/new jersey/", "2/united states/new jersey/middlesex/", "3/united states/new jersey/middlesex/perth amboy/"], "contributor": ["rutgers university libraries"], "date": "1908-02-17", "dates": ["1908-02-17"], "description": ["LARGEST CIRCULATION PERTH AMBOY EVENING NEWS VOL XXVnl NO 169 PERTH AMBOY N J MONDAY FEB 171908 8 PA1E3 TEN CENTS A WEEK \u03b9 LAST EDITION TWO CENTS WATER BOARD MAJORITY OUSTS DEMOCRATS FROM POSITIONS Notices Sent to Two at Runyon PlantJToday CROWELL MAY CET CLERKSHIP It became known thle morning that when the Board of Water Com missioners held a secret session In the council chamber after the regu lar meeting on Wednesday night February 5 at which no newspaper men were allowed the republican majority In the board decided to oust some of the democratic officeholders from the department The first order to this effect was sent to Runyon this morning under instructions from the commissioners by Superintendent Burns to Henry McArdle an engineer and Abram Applegate a firemen 1 The matter It Is said was brought up at the secret meeting just as soon as the reporter had been put out The democratic members objected to ousting the men saying that politics should not enter in a case like this and that some of these men had been in the employ of the water depart ment for years McArdle who has been In the water works department"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-12-01T12:39:00.751Z", "group": ["ndnp/njr", "rutgers-university-libraries-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85035720/1908-02-17/ed-2/?sp=1", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:njr:batch_njr_basil_ver02:data:sn85035720:00279529935:1908021702:0391/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=417&w=313", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:njr:batch_njr_basil_ver02:data:sn85035720:00279529935:1908021702:0391/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=835&w=627", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/njr/batch_njr_basil_ver02/data/sn85035720/00279529935/1908021702/0391.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 1, "language": ["english"], "location": ["middlesex county", "perth amboy", "united states", "new jersey", "middlesex"], "location_city": ["perth amboy"], "location_country": ["united states"], "location_county": ["middlesex"], "location_state": ["new jersey"], "mime_type": ["image/jp2", "application/pdf", "text/xml", "image/jpeg", "image/jpeg", "application/json", "text/plain"], "number": ["5", "3", "0", "2", "sn85035720", "7", "9", "0000000001"], "number_edition": ["2"], "number_lccn": ["sn85035720"], "number_page": ["0000000001"], "number_reel": ["0", "0", "2", "7", "9", "5", "2", "9", "9", "3", "5"], "online_format": ["image", "pdf", "online text"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["chronicling america", "serial and government publications division", "perth amboy evening news (perth amboy, n.j.) 1903-1959"], "partof_collection": ["chronicling america"], "partof_division": ["serial and government publications division"], "partof_title": ["perth amboy evening news (perth amboy, n.j.) 1903-1959"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "resources": [{"files": 1, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85035720/1908-02-17/ed-2/?sp=1"}], "segmentof": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85035720/1908-02-17/ed-2/"], "shelf_id": "1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "subject": ["middlesex county", "perth amboy", "united states", "new jersey", "perth amboy (n.j.)", "newspapers", "middlesex", "middlesex county (n.j.)"], "t